did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.unittitle: Office of the Senior Vice President For Academic Affairs And Provost Records1962-2006
did.abstract: Includes the records of the Office of the Provost which oversees the academic mission of the university.

origination.corpname: State University of New York at Albany. Office of the Provost

did.physloc: The materials are located onsite in the department.

repository.corpname: M. E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives, University at Albany, SUNY

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The office of the Vice President for Academic Affairs was established in 1962 as a successor to the Office of the Dean, which had previously overseen academic programs. As of 2016, the office is referred to as the Office of the Provost, while the Provost's title remains Senior Vice President for Academic Affairs and Provost.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Information
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence and reports of the Vice President for Academic Affairs relating to the establishment, accreditation, and review of academic departments and programs; the closing of the Milne School and phasing out of particular academic programs in the 1970s; SUNYA Deans' Lists, 196670; and administrative policies about probation, transfer students, and faculty salaries. Documents on international programs, enrollment, construction of Dutch and State Quads, the establishment, accreditation and review of various academic departments, the phasing-out of Milne High School, and policies about probation and about transfer students.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of the Collection
arrangement.p: The collection is unprocessed and is likely disorganized. Individual items may be difficult to find.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: All items in this collection were transferred to the University Libraries, M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives.

relatedmaterial.p: Related collections in the M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives can be found in the subject guide for Criminal Justice and Prisons.

accessrestrict.p: Access to this collection is restricted because it is unprocessed. Portions of the collection may contain recent administrative records and/or personally identifiable information. Please contact an archivist for more information.
